I need to identify the line items and values for amounts owed by the entity for goods or services received on credit.

In accounting, these are typically represented by "Accounts Payable" on the balance sheet. This line item specifically tracks the money a company owes to its suppliers or vendors for goods and services purchased on credit.

Looking at the balance sheet provided:

1. I can see the "Accounts Payable" line item
2. The initial amount (as of 2023-12-31) shows 0.00
3. The ending amount (as of 2024-02-02) shows 7566370.00

So the company had zero accounts payable at the beginning of the period, but by the end of the period, they had accumulated 7,566,370.00 in payables to suppliers.
